programmes.show_description: Get behind the wheel of the world's biggest land vehicles as they mine 90,000 tons of coal a day, and hunt for alligators in the Florida swamps.
How do structure movers shift steam turbines that weigh more than ten houses; and how are black boxes built to survive plane crashes?
Saab 900. Mike thinks there's money to be made on a soft-top Saab 900, but it's got a dodgy clutch and woolly steering. Can Elvis get it back to its best?
Subaru BRZ. Mike buys his newest ever car to create a bespoke Scooby BRZ STI. But hopes of a profit are hit with a hefty bill for the turbo and a new exhaust.
Standard 14. Henry and Fuzz head to Bristol to help Russell revive his 1947 Standard 14: a post-war classic with charm, history, and plenty of hidden troubles.
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including Marseille soap and Laguiole pocket knives made?

Hudson Hornet. Wayne chased a Hudson Italia for 38 years before he acquired one from a kindly angel called Hazel, but does she have any other surprises left up her sleeve?
Amelia Island. Wayne heads to The Amelia Island Concours and auctions to sell a 1955 Mercedes-Benz 190sl and 280se Cabriolet, one of which sells for a potential world record price.
Micro Cars. Cute sells and the Bruce Weiner Microcar Museum sale is no exception. With his eye out for a BMW Isetta for his newly married daughter, Wayne is in the right place.
Packards. Wayne heads to an auction of unusual cars, where a 1937 Packard Convertible catches his eye. But how far will he be willing to go to secure a deal?
Ford Fiesta XR2. Mike decides to go back to the 80s and bags a bargain example of one of his dream cars - but can they only spend £1000 on repairs to ensure a profit?
Citroen HY Van. Mike goes to France in search of a retro-cool Citroen HY Van. Edd isn't impressed with his spoils, knowing it will be a costly renovation. But can they find a buyer?
Mini Mark 1 850. Mike finds his favourite iconic British car, a Mini Mark 1, in a garage in Wales. He and Elvis make some radical changes to get it back on the road.
Toyota Landcruiser. Mike and Elvis tackle a classic Toyota Landcruiser. Mike takes a gamble and imports an original 70s one from Japan, not knowing what state it will arrive in.
Ford Escort MK1. Mike picks up a cracking three-door Ford MK1 for £4,500 in an internet auction. Can Edd's restoration help them make a profit on this nifty 70s classic?
Merkur XR4Ti. Mike gets nostalgic in a 1985 Merkur XR4Ti - AKA the Ford Sierra. He has found a rare competition shell model and Ant applies some unique European touches.
Range Rover. Mike buys a bargain Range Rover P38 and Edd sets about mending it. They head to the wilds of Exmoor to give the car a final test drive before searching for a buyer.
Graham Steeler. Henry and Fuzz head to Southend to visit Graham's shed full of bikes and muscle cars. They find a Dutton kit car and rows and rows of rare bikes.
Will Ralph. Henry and Fuzz visit a farm near Colchester with vintage tractors galore. The boys come away with a classic Fordson and some old traffic lights.
Robin Burford. The boys visit Rob, who has an impressive collection of vintage British bikes. They find a BSA Bantam and a classic 1930's Austin Ten automobile.
Paul Webb. Henry and Fuzz visit Paul in the Malvern Hills, a man with a perfectly maintained collection of Japanese motorbikes including a Honda 750 Four.
Frank. Henry and Fuzz are in Moretonhampstead at Frank's motoring museum - home to hundreds of cars, bikes and rare pieces of motoring memorabilia.
Stuart. Henry and Fuzz find a Triumph Terrier in Oxfordshire. Can they breathe life into this little legend and get it back on the road?
Chris. In Cambridgeshire, Henry and Fuzz uncover a Suzuki GSXR Slingshot. Can they tame this superbike and bring it roaring back to life?
Rob. Henry and Fuzz visit Rob in Cambridgeshire and find vintage agricultural gems. Can they get some old workhorses running and make a profit?
Tickled Pink. The Cog respray an Aston Martin Lagonda a shocking pink for Europe's biggest car collector. Richard's daughter Izzy discovers a passion for racing.
Susan hopes restoration expert Steve can bring her once beautiful trinket back to life. Plus, Dominic revives a beloved wedding present, a Georgian peat bucket.
The expert restorers revive a rusty child's bike with a romantic connection, a fluffy monkey that provided support, and a lamp smashed into pieces.
Railway Relics & A Harley Hog. Angus steams into a train treasure trove while helping a bereaved daughter, then hopes to turn a campervan dream into reality with a Harley sale.
In The Trenches. The Misfits return to their claim and find it's been soaked by torrential rain. The Opal Lovers dig a deep trench on their Digger's Gully claim.
Beware Of The Locals. Camille and Hannah hunt on Springbank Island in the middle of Lake Burley Griffin. Andrew and Mish make some illuminating finds.
Monster In The Abyss. Experts investigate the disappearance of people who have gone missing while swimming in the Triangle. Some locals believe a sea monster is responsible.
US Navy Vs The Triangle. New discoveries might finally explain the truth behind one of the Triangle's most infamous mysteries, when 306 US Navy crewmen vanished without a trace.
